<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="252" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[115,754,288,424]" pageId="1" pageNumber="252">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[115,237,288,309]" pageId="1" pageNumber="252">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[115,214,288,309]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="252">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. –
</emphasis>
Ocellar setae absent; third tergite without dark brown patches; surstylus with ca. 27 strong setae on inner surface (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[139,183,1040,1061]" captionTargetBox="[251,1362,195,992]" captionTargetId="figure-75@2.[224,1381,169,1007]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 3–7. Luzonimyia flavipedes, new species, male: 3, head; 4, sixth tergite (6th te), epandrium (epan), cercus (cerc) and surstylus (sur) (lateral view); 5, surstylus (inner view); 6, sixth sternite? (6th st?), hypandrium (hypa), decasternum (dec), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral view); 7, sixth sternite? (6th st?), hypandrium (hypa), decasternum (dec), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5340283" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5340283/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="252">Figs. 4, 5</figureCitation>
); cercus nearly triangular (
<figureCitation box="[438,503,345,366]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[139,183,1040,1061]" captionTargetBox="[251,1362,195,992]" captionTargetId="figure-75@2.[224,1381,169,1007]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 3–7. Luzonimyia flavipedes, new species, male: 3, head; 4, sixth tergite (6th te), epandrium (epan), cercus (cerc) and surstylus (sur) (lateral view); 5, surstylus (inner view); 6, sixth sternite? (6th st?), hypandrium (hypa), decasternum (dec), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral view); 7, sixth sternite? (6th st?), hypandrium (hypa), decasternum (dec), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5340283" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5340283/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="252">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); aedeagus (basiphallus) expanded and extroverted in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[515,572,374,395]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[139,183,1040,1061]" captionTargetBox="[251,1362,195,992]" captionTargetId="figure-75@2.[224,1381,169,1007]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 3–7. Luzonimyia flavipedes, new species, male: 3, head; 4, sixth tergite (6th te), epandrium (epan), cercus (cerc) and surstylus (sur) (lateral view); 5, surstylus (inner view); 6, sixth sternite? (6th st?), hypandrium (hypa), decasternum (dec), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral view); 7, sixth sternite? (6th st?), hypandrium (hypa), decasternum (dec), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5340283" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5340283/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="252">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
), triangular basally in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[269,329,403,424]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[139,183,1040,1061]" captionTargetBox="[251,1362,195,992]" captionTargetId="figure-75@2.[224,1381,169,1007]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 3–7. Luzonimyia flavipedes, new species, male: 3, head; 4, sixth tergite (6th te), epandrium (epan), cercus (cerc) and surstylus (sur) (lateral view); 5, surstylus (inner view); 6, sixth sternite? (6th st?), hypandrium (hypa), decasternum (dec), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral view); 7, sixth sternite? (6th st?), hypandrium (hypa), decasternum (dec), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5340283" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5340283/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="252">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
